## Appendix A: Quick Reference

### HFT Latency Targets

| Component | Target | Acceptable |
|-----------|--------|------------|
| Signal generation | < 1ms | < 10ms |
| Risk check | < 100us | < 1ms |
| Order submission | < 100us | < 1ms |
| State update | < 10us | < 100us |

### Scalability Rules of Thumb

| Metric | Single User | 1K Users | 100K Users |
|--------|-------------|----------|------------|
| Memory per user | 100MB | 100GB total | External store |
| DB connections | 1 | Connection pool | PgBouncer |
| Compute | 1 core | 16 cores | Kubernetes |
| Storage | Local | NAS | S3/MinIO |

### State Management Principles

1. **Single source of truth**: One authoritative location for each state
2. **Idempotent updates**: Same input always produces same state
3. **Audit trail**: Every state change is logged with timestamp and cause
4. **Reconciliation**: Automated checks between redundant state stores
